<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06348032 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06348032 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  STOCK; CHART  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Japanese stock prices rallied in heavy trading today, sending one index to itsbiggest gain of the year on the Tokyo Stock Exchange.;   The 225-issue NikkeiStock Average rose 1,042.33 points, or 4.80 percent, ending a roller-coasterweek at 22,754.90. A 4.8 percent rise in the Dow would mean a 140-point jump.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TOKYO STOCKS SOAR; DOW MOVES UP  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Chart attached at end of article  </MEMO><TEXT>     On Thursday, the Nikkei average rose 209.67 points, or 0.96 percent, aftera five-day drop totaling 1,166.54 points.;   Today's advance in the Nikkei wasthe largest single-day rise in points this year, exceeding the previous surgeof 1,004.11 recorded on Jan. 17, which had come on expectations of an quickend to the Gulf war.;   It was the eighth-largest ever.;   Traders said thatdespite pessimism about the economy and the poor performance of Japanesecompanies, they believed stock prices had fallen too sharply earlier in theweek.;   In New York, the stock market chalked up a broad gain today,following through on Thursday's rally.;   The Dow Jones average of 30industrials rose 15.42 points to 2,910.55 in the first half-hour of trading.;  Analysts said investors were heartened by government reports in recent dayssuggesting that the state of the economy might not be quite as gloomy as hadbeen widely supposed.;   In today's economic news, the Labor Departmentreported that the Consumer Price Index rose 0.4 percent in November, slightlyabove consensus expectations.;   But the figure still indicated thatinflationary pressures weren't heating up in any drastic way.;   Through thefirst 11 months of the year, the CPI has registered inflation at a 2.9 percentrate.;   On Thursday, the Dow average climbed 29.75 points to 2,895.13.;  Advancing issues outnumbered declines by more than 5 to 3 on the NYSE, with1,029 up, 595 down and 539 unchanged.;   Big Board volume came to an estimated192.93 million shares as of 4 p.m. EST, against 206.01 million at the samepoint in the previous session.; THE MARKETS; In trading    today:; ...; TheDow Jones average rose  15.42 points by 10 a.m. EST.; ...; January crudefutures rose 45 cents to $19.96 a barrel.; ...; In Tokyo, the dollar closed at128.73 yen, down 0.17 yen.; ...; In Zurich, gold was $358.80, down $1.15 anounce.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Street  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911213  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1F  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  CHART  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  378  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, December 13, 199100348032,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>